{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"## What\nContinuous alerting for the two post-cutover silent-failure modes of the Gerrit->GitHub mirror:\nreplication failing (GitHub main stops advancing while Gerrit main moves), and the\ngerrit-mirror-lock-main ruleset being mutated/deleted out-of-band (drift to unprotected).\n\n## Design (two independent, secretless watchers)\n- A tested Python module (src/rebar/mirror_guard.py) holds the verdict LOGIC + I/O + a CLI, driven\n  by a scheduled GitHub Actions workflow (the PRIMARY guardian): native GITHUB_TOKEN authenticates\n  the GitHub Rulesets API fetch; the Gerrit main SHA is read ANONYMOUSLY (public REST); no new secret.\n- A lightweight bash probe in observability.sh is the SECONDARY, house-style replication watcher:\n  it compares the anon Gerrit main SHA vs the anon GitHub main SHA (git ls-remote) and publishes a\n  CloudWatch metric (no auth, matching the S5 replication probe) -> a Terraform alarm -> SNS.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] src/rebar/mirror_guard.py exposes replication_verdict(gerrit_sha, github_sha) returning an in-sync/diverged verdict.\n- [ ] src/rebar/mirror_guard.py exposes ruleset_verdict(ruleset) enforcing the full lock contract (active, target=branch, refs/heads/main, rules update+deletion+non_fast_forward, bypass = DeployKey only).\n- [ ] src/rebar/mirror_guard.py provides thin I/O fetchers for the Gerrit main SHA (anon), the GitHub main SHA, and the GitHub ruleset (GITHUB_TOKEN from env).\n- [ ] python -m rebar.mirror_guard runs both checks, prints a JSON result, exits non-zero when unhealthy.\n- [ ] Behavioral tests cover in-sync vs diverged for replication_verdict.\n- [ ] Behavioral tests cover locked vs each ruleset drift mutation (disabled, missing rule, extra bypass, wrong ref, deleted).\n- [ ] Contractual tests pin the verdict output schema.\n- [ ] Contractual tests pin the CLI exit codes.\n- [ ] .github/workflows/mirror-guard.yml runs the CLI on a cron schedule plus manual dispatch.\n- [ ] The workflow grants the job permissions: administration: read so the Actions GITHUB_TOKEN can read the repo ruleset; if org policy disallows that, a fine-grained PAT (administration:read) stored as an Actions secret is the documented fallback.\n- [ ] The workflow fails (producing a notification) when either check is unhealthy.\n- [ ] infra/scripts/observability.sh publishes the rebar/host:mirror_out_of_sync metric via aws cloudwatch put-metric-data (dimensionless), comparing the anon Gerrit and GitHub main SHAs in bash.\n- [ ] infra/terraform/monitoring_ws7.tf defines a CloudWatch alarm on that metric wired to the rebar-gerrit-alerts SNS topic.\n- [ ] The guardian is verified LIVE reporting healthy plus locked against production.\n- [ ] A simulated ruleset drift is detected by the guardian, then reverted.\n\n## Files\n- src/rebar/mirror_guard.py, tests/unit/test_mirror_guard.py, .github/workflows/mirror-guard.yml, infra/scripts/observability.sh, infra/terraform/monitoring_ws7.tf"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782948133077859001,"uuid":"ae2c9184-18cf-4736-af6f-6eb120f8f626"}